18:49.500 --> 18:52.200 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It will deal with some basic
things, like the individual
mandate, the employer mandate,

18:52.200 --> 18:55.300 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
state flexibility in allowing
states to have greater options.

18:55.300 --> 18:59.133 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
When the Affordable Care Act was
passed, it took all the control
of health care to Washington,

18:59.133 --> 19:01.300 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
D.C., away from all the states.

19:01.300 --> 19:05.133 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
And so we want to be
able to return some of
that control back, when
prices were much cheaper

19:05.133 --> 19:08.300 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
in the time before, when the
Affordable Care Act was passed.

19:08.300 --> 19:09.500 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
So those will be
the basic elements.

19:09.500 --> 19:11.933 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
There will be some other
smaller parts to it.

19:11.933 --> 19:15.500 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It's basically the employer
mandate, individual
mandate, and state control
vs. federal control.

19:15.500 --> 19:20.500 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Well, as you
know, Senator, Democrats and
even a number of Republicans

19:22.500 --> 19:25.333 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
are saying what's being called
skinny repeal, which is, I
gather, what you're referring

19:25.333 --> 19:26.333 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
to...

19:26.333 --> 19:27.333 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

19:27.333 --> 19:29.300 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
JAMES LANKFORD: Right.

19:29.300 --> 19:32.100 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: ... would leave,
what, more than 15 million
Americans without coverage.

19:32.100 --> 19:35.533 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Other versions would leave many
more millions without coverage.

19:35.533 --> 19:39.133 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Any one of these versions,
we're told, would raise
the cost of premiums.

19:39.133 --> 19:41.200 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
How do you explain a
vote to support that?

19:41.200 --> 19:42.866 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

19:42.866 --> 19:44.200 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
JAMES LANKFORD: So,
again, today's vote
is not the final vote.

19:44.200 --> 19:45.833 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
I understand that.

19:45.833 --> 19:48.633 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
They're trying to score
something that's not
finished by any means.

19:48.633 --> 19:50.133 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
So, that's one big piece of it.

19:50.133 --> 19:52.266 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
The other one is to be able to
look at how CBO scores this.

19:52.266 --> 19:57.033 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
CBO scores -- they basically
assume that if there is not a
mandate to buy it, most people

19:57.033 --> 20:00.533 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
won't buy the insurance products
that are put out there under
the Affordable Care Act.

20:00.533 --> 20:04.066 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So, literally, there's
nine million people right
now on the exchanges.

20:04.066 --> 20:09.066 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
They assume 22 million
people won't have insurance
in the days ahead based
on them changing this.

20:11.066 --> 20:13.366 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Now, this may seem odd, and it
only works in an economist's
mind, that only nine million

20:13.366 --> 20:16.366 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
people have it, 22 million
people lose it in that sense.

20:16.366 --> 20:18.400 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
But here's what's
really going on.

20:18.400 --> 20:21.200 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Of the mine million people
that are having it, CBO says,
if they're given the choice

20:21.200 --> 20:25.166 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
to be able to buy it, many of
the individuals don't want to
buy that product, and they only

20:25.166 --> 20:27.933 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
buy it because they're
forced to buy that product.

20:27.933 --> 20:30.000 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
So that's the number
that's sitting out there.

20:30.000 --> 20:34.566 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I would also say, in my state,
CBO never saw in their original
estimates when the Affordable

20:34.566 --> 20:39.566 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Care Act passed that in my
state the insurance rates would
go up over 200 percent for the

20:40.766 --> 20:42.833 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
individuals that were
buying their insurance.

20:42.833 --> 20:45.333 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So CBO is making their best
guess, but I can assure you they
don't always guess correctly.

20:45.333 --> 20:47.633 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
No one can really see
into the future on that.

20:47.633 --> 20:50.733 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So they're laying out an
economist's view vs. practically
what's actually happening

20:50.733 --> 20:52.866 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
on the ground.

20:52.866 --> 20:55.200 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Well, we know
that hospital officials in
Oklahoma have said if one of

20:55.200 --> 21:00.200 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
the versions of this were to
pass, that they thought it would
be devastating on their ability

21:00.200 --> 21:04.633 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
to take care of low-income
individuals, whether on
Medicaid or otherwise.

21:04.633 --> 21:07.433 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
What do you say to them,
the folks in your own state?

21:07.433 --> 21:08.666 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

21:08.666 --> 21:10.166 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
JAMES LANKFORD: Yes,
same thing, Judy.

21:10.166 --> 21:12.233 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Obviously, they're looking
at just part of a plan.

21:12.233 --> 21:14.666 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And I know that my Democratic
colleagues have been very good
for distributing bits and pieces

21:14.666 --> 21:18.133 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
of plans and saying here is the
whole plan, without actually
putting the full picture

21:18.133 --> 21:23.133 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
out there for individuals to be
able to see how the stability
works, how aspects of it

21:23.600 --> 21:25.600 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
work.

21:25.600 --> 21:26.933 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
They will just put out and
say, this is going to be a cut
that happens to this particular

21:26.933 --> 21:27.933 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
area.

21:27.933 --> 21:29.400 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
What will happen?

21:29.400 --> 21:30.666 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Immediately, they respond back,
well, that will be dramatic.

21:30.666 --> 21:32.666 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Let me give you a for
instance on Medicaid.

21:32.666 --> 21:35.900 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I hear a lot of talk about
how Medicaid goes down in
one of the earlier proposals.

21:35.900 --> 21:40.200 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Medicaid actually increases
every year for the next eight
years in that proposal by twice

21:40.200 --> 21:44.900 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
the rate of inflation, and
then nine years from now it
increases at only the rate of

21:44.900 --> 21:46.900 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
inflation.

21:46.900 --> 21:50.266 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
That's put out by my Democratic
colleagues as a big cut in
Medicaid because nine years

21:50.266 --> 21:54.833 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
from now it doesn't increase
as fast, but every single
year it's increasing, and for

21:54.833 --> 21:57.333 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
the next eight years
it increases twice
as fast as inflation.

21:57.333 --> 22:01.200 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Senator, I want
to change the subject and ask
you about the attorney general,

22:01.200 --> 22:03.300 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
Jeff Sessions.

22:03.300 --> 22:07.200 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
As you know, President Trump
has been publicly criticizing
him for the last several days,

22:09.233 --> 22:12.600 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
mainly because the attorney
general recused himself from
the Russia investigation.

22:12.600 --> 22:16.600 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
What do you make of
the president's public
campaign against him?

22:16.600 --> 22:18.100 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

22:18.100 --> 22:19.266 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JAMES LANKFORD: Yes, it's
something I would never do.

22:19.266 --> 22:20.500 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Obviously, the president
is the president.

22:20.500 --> 22:22.533 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
He can lead his staff
however he chooses.

22:22.533 --> 22:24.500 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But I would never say to my
staff in a public setting
that there is a problem.

22:24.500 --> 22:27.900 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
If I have a problem with a
staff member, they will sit
down with me in my office and we

22:27.900 --> 22:29.400 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
will sit down and work it out.

22:29.400 --> 22:31.400 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And if we can't work it
out, then they will leave.

22:31.400 --> 22:33.933 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But that's something we are
going to work out in private,
not in a public setting.

22:33.933 --> 22:37.433 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And, quite frankly, Jeff
Sessions had to recuse himself.

22:37.433 --> 22:40.066 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
That's something all the legal
counsel in the Department
of Justice, once he joined

22:40.066 --> 22:43.533 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
as the attorney general,
sat down with him, laid
out the law of the statute.

22:43.533 --> 22:45.600 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Everyone looked at it's.

22:45.600 --> 22:47.500 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Everyone read it exactly
the same way, that Jeff
needed to recuse himself.

22:47.500 --> 22:49.666 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Now, did Jeff understand
that before he got there?

22:49.666 --> 22:53.366 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
No, I don't think he
did, but once he was in
that spot, sitting down
with all the attorneys,

22:53.366 --> 22:55.466 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
he understand full well
that he had to do that.

22:55.466 --> 22:58.566 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I understand that frustrates
the president, but it was
the right thing to do.

22:58.566 --> 23:03.566 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: What would
it mean if the president
were to fire the attorney
general or if Jeff

23:05.966 --> 23:09.133 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Sessions were to step down
because of this pressure
from the president?

23:09.133 --> 23:11.633 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

23:11.633 --> 23:12.433 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JAMES LANKFORD: Well, there
would be -- obviously,
the president -- doesn't
have to be just pressure

23:12.433 --> 23:14.500 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
from the president.

23:14.500 --> 23:16.500 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The president chooses who his
staff is, and they all serve at
the pleasure of the president.

23:16.500 --> 23:19.833 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So, if any point the president
is uncomfortable with Jeff
Sessions and his leadership, he

23:19.833 --> 23:20.966 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
can choose to remove him.

23:20.966 --> 23:22.733 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
That's what the
president does for that.

23:22.733 --> 23:24.700 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
So, that's not the issue.

23:24.700 --> 23:27.633 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The issue is then going
through the process, going
through all of the nomination.

23:27.633 --> 23:32.433 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Getting through all that aspect
again starting all over again
and getting someone in will

23:32.433 --> 23:34.433 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
take months and months.

23:34.433 --> 23:37.700 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Right now, the attorney general
is getting a good stride and
dealing with U.S. attorneys

23:37.700 --> 23:40.866 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
around the country, getting
with his staff, getting on board
with different investigations

23:40.866 --> 23:42.600 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
that need to be done.

23:42.600 --> 23:44.866 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
So, I hate to be able to
lose that progress that
is happening right now.

23:44.866 --> 23:47.966 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
JUDY WOODRUFF: What
would it mean for the
Russia investigation
if that were to happen?

23:47.966 --> 23:49.900 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

23:49.900 --> 23:51.833 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JAMES LANKFORD: It
wouldn't change the Russia
investigation at all.

23:51.833 --> 23:54.666 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Jeff is completely disconnected
from what is happening in
the Russia investigation.

23:54.666 --> 23:56.366 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
He's recused himself.

23:56.366 --> 23:58.466 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
We have had numerous
interactions with
people in the DOJ.

23:58.466 --> 24:00.833 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
He's not tried to interfere
in that in any way.

24:00.833 --> 24:03.066 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
That's already in the special
counsel's responsibility.

24:03.066 --> 24:05.366 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
So, it doesn't change
that investigation at all.

24:05.366 --> 24:09.300 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
JUDY WOODRUFF: And,
finally, Senator, the
president's announcement
by Twitter yesterday

24:09.300 --> 24:13.666 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
that he wants to ban individuals
who are transgender from
serving in the military?

24:13.666 --> 24:16.266 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

24:16.266 --> 24:17.900 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JAMES LANKFORD: Yes, we're
trying to get additional
details on what he means by
that, the implementation.

24:17.900 --> 24:20.133 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
Obviously, the Pentagon
was unaware of an
announcement like that.

24:20.133 --> 24:24.766 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The Pentagon was already in a
six-month review dealing with
transgenders in the military,

24:24.766 --> 24:28.933 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
what that means as far as
costs, unit cohesion, deployment
capabilities, what that means.

24:28.933 --> 24:30.433 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Would
you support the ban?

24:30.433 --> 24:32.500 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

24:32.500 --> 24:34.300 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JAMES LANKFORD: Well, again,
I'm waiting for that six-month
review to come back from the

24:34.300 --> 24:36.333 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
military officials.

24:36.333 --> 24:39.733 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We open up our military to
all aspects for any individual
that comes into the military

24:39.733 --> 24:41.766 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
that wants to be able to serve.

24:41.766 --> 24:45.300 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
There are unique issues, not
just with a gay soldier or
member of the military, but of

24:45.300 --> 24:46.733 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
someone who is in transition.

24:46.733 --> 24:48.766 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
You deal with medical issues.

24:48.766 --> 24:51.866 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
You deal with a lot of
additional costs and
implementation, what
happens in a unit based

24:51.866 --> 24:54.433 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
on that, because that's
-- as you know, that's
not a single surgery.

24:54.433 --> 24:56.133 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
That's a series of
surgeries that happens.

24:56.133 --> 24:58.200 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And it's a long time for them
to be away from their unit.

24:58.200 --> 25:01.566 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So, there are additional
questions that are there that
are unique to that, whether that

25:01.566 --> 25:05.800 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
individual should go through
transition before they come
into the military or after.

25:05.800 --> 25:08.433 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
All of those things are still
up in the air, and the military
is walking through that right

25:08.433 --> 25:10.033 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
now.

25:10.033 --> 25:12.166 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Senator
James Lankford of
Oklahoma, we thank you.

25:12.166 --> 25:13.166 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

25:13.166 --> 25:14.166 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
JAMES LANKFORD: Great.

25:14.166 --> 25:16.200 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
Thank you.

