McNulty insisted I find out
for myself for how many years
they had been coming, 21 years,

26:42.166 --> 26:43.333 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
22 years.

26:43.333 --> 26:46.266 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
You're the new champ, 24.

26:46.266 --> 26:48.266 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
That beats everybody.

26:48.266 --> 26:52.500 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Provincetown has a year-round
population of just under 3,000,
which swells to 10,000 in

26:52.500 --> 26:54.566 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
the summer.

26:54.566 --> 26:58.566 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Add the estimated four to five
million tourists that visit the
Cape every year, and you have

26:59.700 --> 27:01.833 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
got the poster child
for peak demand.

27:01.833 --> 27:05.833 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JOY MCNULTY, Owner, Lobster
Pot: How do you run a business
where all your kids work for

27:05.833 --> 27:09.666 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
you, all your grandchildren
work for you, and I don't
know if I can open next year?

27:09.666 --> 27:11.800 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
How could you do that?

27:11.800 --> 27:16.366 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
PAUL SOLMAN: The problem
is getting Americans, of
any vintage, to do the
back of the housework.

27:18.366 --> 27:22.133 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So businesses here rely on
foreigners, says Jane Nichols
Bishop, known as Mama Visa to

27:22.733 --> 27:24.833 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
the workers.

27:24.833 --> 27:28.333 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JANE NICHOLS BISHOP, Owner, Peak
Season Workforce: In a seasonal
economy, there are usually not

27:28.333 --> 27:32.333 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
enough American workers
to fill all of the jobs.

27:32.333 --> 27:34.200 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
They're not year-round jobs.

27:34.200 --> 27:37.333 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
So the Congress allowed
something called an H-2B.

27:37.333 --> 27:42.333 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
PAUL SOLMAN: Which allows
half-year work if no
one else can be found,
and must be renewed

27:44.200 --> 27:47.833 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
annually, for temporary
positions like hotel
housekeepers and
restaurant workers.

27:47.833 --> 27:52.833 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
In the past, Congress has
made 66,000 of these visas
available annually nationwide.

27:54.866 --> 27:59.866 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And workers with previous H-2Bs,
like almost everyone here,
could return without being

28:01.266 --> 28:03.533 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
counted against that
limit, but not this summer.

28:03.533 --> 28:08.533 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JANE NICHOLS BISHOP: Congress
didn't pass a returning worker
exemption in the continuing

28:10.100 --> 28:12.866 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
resolution to fund the
government, which is
where it's always been.

28:12.866 --> 28:17.866 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
And because they didn't
do that, the number
of visas available was
greatly restricted.

28:19.833 --> 28:24.333 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So there are not enough visas
for all the employers to
bring in their temporary work

28:24.333 --> 28:26.333 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
force.

28:26.333 --> 28:30.333 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
PAUL SOLMAN: The Department
of Homeland Security did add
another 15,000 visas last week.

28:32.000 --> 28:35.400 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
But with the exemption
gone, the total number
of H-2Bs is way down.

28:37.433 --> 28:40.600 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And with employers now having
to prove irreparable harm to get
one of the additional visas, the

28:42.500 --> 28:45.666 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
paperwork that might,
or might not, get a
worker in has mushroomed.

28:47.733 --> 28:51.633 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
What an irony for a supposedly
anti-red tape administration,
says Congressman Bill Keating,

28:53.600 --> 28:56.600 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
who represents the Cape, though,
of course, he's from a district
even bluer than its fish.

28:56.600 --> 28:58.466 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
REP.

28:58.466 --> 28:59.700 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
BILL KEATING (D),
Massachusetts: The fix is
staring us right in the face.

28:59.700 --> 29:01.833 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
It's just raise the cap
on returning workers.

29:01.833 --> 29:03.833 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
We have done it for
the last 11 years.

29:03.833 --> 29:05.000 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
It works.

29:05.000 --> 29:05.833 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
PAUL SOLMAN: But
they just did it now.

29:05.833 --> 29:06.833 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
REP.

29:06.833 --> 29:08.866 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
BILL KEATING: No, they didn't.

29:08.866 --> 29:12.833 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
They created a whole new series
of regulations and requirements
that would scare any small

29:14.233 --> 29:18.200 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
business person into not using
this because of politics.

29:19.333 --> 29:21.366 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
PAUL SOLMAN: Really?

29:21.366 --> 29:25.300 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JOY MCNULTY: It's impossible to
run a business when you don't
know if you're getting 43 of

29:25.300 --> 29:27.000 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
your 96 people.

29:27.000 --> 29:28.733 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
The rest of them
are all Americans.

29:28.733 --> 29:31.266 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
This year, we were
open six weeks late.

29:31.266 --> 29:33.833 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Last week, we opened
six weeks late.

29:33.833 --> 29:36.333 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Next year, we may
not open at all.

29:36.333 --> 29:38.433 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
We don't know.

29:38.433 --> 29:42.333 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
PAUL SOLMAN: Gui Yingling got
none of the requested 26 H-2B
workers for nearby Bubala's

29:42.933 --> 29:44.433 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
By the Bay.

29:44.433 --> 29:45.366 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
GUI YINGLING, Bubala's By the
Bay: It's been next impossible.

29:45.366 --> 29:46.366 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
We have had to close days.

29:46.366 --> 29:48.466 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
We have had to shorten hours.

29:48.466 --> 29:52.500 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
PAUL SOLMAN: And a corollary
problem, say restaurateurs
like Yingling and Mac Hay of

29:53.666 --> 29:55.700 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Mac's Seafood, is that
if and when they close:

29:55.700 --> 30:00.300 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MAC HAY, Owner, Mac's Seafood:
I would have to lay off way
more than half of the work

30:01.033 --> 30:02.333 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
force that I have now.

30:02.333 --> 30:03.600 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
PAUL SOLMAN: American workers.

30:03.600 --> 30:05.566 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
MAC HAY: An American work force.

30:05.566 --> 30:08.133 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
PAUL SOLMAN: And, look, they
say, it's not for lack of
trying, to recruit natives, that

30:08.133 --> 30:10.033 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
is.

30:10.033 --> 30:13.800 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
In fact, the H-2B application
requires employers to
offer the jobs locally.

30:13.800 --> 30:16.633 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
JOY MCNULTY: I advertise
on the Internet.

30:16.633 --> 30:18.833 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
I advertise in every job fair.

30:18.833 --> 30:21.566 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
We advertise in every newspaper.

30:21.566 --> 30:24.966 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
Everyone on the entire
Cape knows that we're
all looking for help.

30:24.966 --> 30:26.600 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
There's nobody here.

30:26.600 --> 30:31.300 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
They will not take
seasonal dishwashing and
cook jobs for anything.

30:33.233 --> 30:36.233 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
PAUL SOLMAN: But wait a second,
counters H-2B skeptic Jessica
Vaughan of the Center for

30:36.233 --> 30:38.366 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Immigration Studies.

30:38.366 --> 30:39.333 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
JESSICA VAUGHAN, Center
for Immigration Studies:
I don't think there's
any such thing as a

30:39.333 --> 30:41.433 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
job an American won't do.

30:41.433 --> 30:46.266 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
There are millions of workers
in the United States who are
not employed, and we need to

30:48.400 --> 30:51.500 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
find a way to match them
up with some of these
opportunities as well.

30:51.500 --> 30:55.333 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
PAUL SOLMAN: Employers just
aren't trying hard enough,
Vaughan insists, while driving

30:55.333 --> 30:58.466 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
down wages, and maybe
even working conditions.

30:58.466 --> 31:02.300 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
More and more, she says,
teens and those with a high
school diploma at best:

31:02.300 --> 31:07.300 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JESSICA VAUGHAN: Employers
should look to those workers
first before they take the easy

31:08.466 --> 31:10.300 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
route out, and bring in
workers from overseas.

31:10.300 --> 31:12.766 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
MAC HAY: I have no
issue, no problem.

31:12.766 --> 31:15.366 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
I would prefer to do that.

31:15.366 --> 31:19.533 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Trying to bring workers
from Jamaica or Mexico is
incredibly challenging,
incredibly expensive.

31:21.533 --> 31:25.700 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
PAUL SOLMAN: Mac Hay worked in
kitchens on the Cape since he
was 12, now owns six businesses,

31:26.833 --> 31:28.233 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
restaurants and seafood markets.

31:28.233 --> 31:30.233 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
The pay?

31:30.233 --> 31:34.233 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MAC HAY: A dishwasher is
$12.50 to a cook can make $17,
$18 an hour, plus overtime.

31:34.966 --> 31:36.400 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
PAUL SOLMAN: Not bad.

31:36.400 --> 31:38.133 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
So why aren't these
summer jobs for students?

31:38.133 --> 31:42.633 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
MAC HAY: The majority of
them leave August 12 or
August 13 or August 14.

31:42.633 --> 31:44.733 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
We have a 10-week season.

31:44.733 --> 31:46.800 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
It runs through Labor Day.

31:46.800 --> 31:51.166 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I can't lose more than half
my work force with three weeks
to go, with 30 percent of

31:51.800 --> 31:53.333 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
my season left.

31:53.333 --> 31:55.400 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
PAUL SOLMAN: And nonstudents
who are un- or under-employed?

31:55.400 --> 31:59.033 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MAC HAY: Americans, they
don't want to relocate
their life for six months.

31:59.033 --> 32:02.833 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
They don't want to move down,
but if they're willing to do
it, I'm more than happy to hire

32:02.833 --> 32:04.866 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
them.

32:04.866 --> 32:08.833 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
PAUL SOLMAN: Like Joy McNulty
at the Lobster Pot, Mac Hay
utterly depends on visa workers.

32:10.000 --> 32:11.966 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Egan Bonny's been with
him for 10 seasons.

32:11.966 --> 32:15.866 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
EGAN BONNY, Mac's Seafood: I do
cleaning, clean the restaurant
and do all kind of jobs

32:17.000 --> 32:19.233 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
which no American kids
would come and do.

32:19.233 --> 32:21.466 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
This grease job here,
fill the grease job.

32:21.466 --> 32:26.466 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
No young kid's going to come
around and do this stuff.

32:27.700 --> 32:28.933 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Keep everything nice,
clean the bathroom.

32:28.933 --> 32:30.033 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
PAUL SOLMAN: Because
they're spoiled?

32:30.033 --> 32:31.033 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
EGAN BONNY: They're spoiled.

32:31.033 --> 32:32.033 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Seriously, they're spoiled.

32:32.033 --> 32:33.566 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
PAUL SOLMAN: Really?

32:33.566 --> 32:35.633 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
There is no wage at which
they would do these jobs?

32:35.633 --> 32:38.633 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
GUI YINGLING: I have hired
every employee who has tried
to walk through the door.

32:38.633 --> 32:40.733 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
I have advertised.

32:40.733 --> 32:43.633 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Most of them don't show up, is
the truth, once I hire them.

32:43.633 --> 32:45.166 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
It's pretty incredible.

32:45.166 --> 32:48.100 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
I have had 17 employees no-show
this season, after being hired.

32:48.100 --> 32:51.600 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
PAUL SOLMAN: Now, we did
run into one underemployed
American worker.

32:51.600 --> 32:53.333 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
So what are you
doing this summer?

32:53.333 --> 32:55.466 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
CLAIRE VAUGHAN, Student:
I'm working in a church
nursery every Sunday.

32:55.466 --> 32:57.833 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
PAUL SOLMAN: And you have
applied for other jobs.

32:57.833 --> 32:58.833 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
CLAIRE VAUGHAN:
Yes, that's right.

32:58.833 --> 33:00.400 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
PAUL SOLMAN: And?

33:00.400 --> 33:02.400 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
CLAIRE VAUGHAN: I have not
heard back from any of them.

33:02.400 --> 33:05.133 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
PAUL SOLMAN: Seventeen-year
old Claire Vaughan lives
about two hours from the Cape.

33:05.133 --> 33:07.666 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
PAUL SOLMAN: So now,
why aren't you here?

33:07.666 --> 33:11.266 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
CLAIRE VAUGHAN: I didn't
know there were jobs here.

33:11.266 --> 33:13.366 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
I had no idea you could do that.

33:13.366 --> 33:16.433 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
PAUL SOLMAN: Claire Vaughan
happens to be the daughter
of our immigration skeptic.

33:16.433 --> 33:19.333 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
CLAIRE VAUGHAN: Now
that I know about it,
I will definitely look.

33:19.333 --> 33:23.033 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
PAUL SOLMAN: But it turned
that she, like most students,
would have to leave before

33:23.033 --> 33:24.500 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
the season was over.

33:24.500 --> 33:27.100 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And her parents didn't want
her living on the Cape.

33:27.100 --> 33:28.833 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
And so we come to
the bottom line.

33:28.833 --> 33:33.833 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
Bubala's is down 10
percent and may actually
lose money this year.

33:34.700 --> 33:35.666 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Mac Hay worries about next year.

33:35.666 --> 33:37.733 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
And the Lobster Pot?

33:37.733 --> 33:42.733 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
In the six weeks it had to
close, it bought a lot fewer
lobsters from local fishermen,

33:43.833 --> 33:46.166 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
hired fewer Americans
for fewer hours.

33:46.166 --> 33:50.433 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JOY MCNULTY: All of the
Americans are out of
work for six extra weeks.

33:50.433 --> 33:55.433 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The state doesn't get the
taxes, the vendors don't get
the work, nothing happens here,

33:56.300 --> 33:58.433 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
and the town collapses.

33:58.433 --> 34:03.433 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
But my people have been with me
for 20, 25 years, a lot of them.

34:04.366 --> 34:07.066 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
What harm is that to anybody?

34:07.066 --> 34:09.300 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
We just want to
run a restaurant.

34:09.300 --> 34:13.266 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
PAUL SOLMAN: For the
"PBS NewsHour," this is
economics correspondent
Paul Solman, reporting

34:13.266 --> 34:18.266 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
from Cape Cod.

